  "prompt": "What was the result of today's CodeNation intern interview at NSIT?",
  "response": "I'm sorry, but I don't have access to real-time information or specific details about individual interview results. To find out the outcome of today's CodeNation intern interview at NSIT, I recommend the following steps:\n\n1. **Check Your Email:** Organizations often send interview results via email. Make sure to look through your inbox, including your spam or junk folders.\n\n2. **Visit the Official Website:** Sometimes, updates or announcements about interview results are posted on the official NSIT or CodeNation websites.\n\n3. **Contact the Recruitment Team:** Reach out directly to the NSIT admissions or recruitment team through their official contact channels. They can provide you with the most accurate and up-to-date information regarding your interview status.\n\n4. **Check Your Application Portal:** If you applied through an online portal, log in to see if there are any updates or notifications regarding your application.\n\nBest of luck with your application!",
